videos.description: Bennett Moehring kickoff for 63 yds , Carlos Henderson return for 82 yds to the Navy 16
videos.headline: Louisana Tech gets energized early with electrifing kickoff return for 63 yards

videos.description: Ryan Higgins gets Louisiana Tech on the board first with a short touchdown run.
videos.headline: Louisiana Tech scores early TD

videos.description: Calvin Cass Jr. run for no gain to the LaTch 48 Calvin Cass Jr. fumbled, recovered by LaTch Prince Sam
videos.headline: Louisana Tech recovers the fumble off the Navy botched pitch

videos.description: Zach Abey pass complete to Chris High for 38 yds to the LaTch 4 for a 1ST down
videos.headline: Z. Abey pass,to C. High for 38 yds for a 1ST down

videos.description: Zach Abey keeps the ball and powers his way into the end zone from three yards out to get Navy on the board and cut into Louisiana Tech's lead at 10-7.
videos.headline: Abey punches it in to get Navy on the board

videos.description: After Navy finally gets on the board, Louisiana Tech answers with the quick pass out to Trent Taylor who goes 19 yards to the end zone reestablishing the Bulldogs' 10-point lead at 17-7.
videos.headline: Quick out pass turns into 19-yard TD for LA Tech

videos.description: Navy quarterback Zach Abey looks deep and finds a wide open Darryl Bonner who goes the rest of the way for a 64-yard touchdown to get the Midshipmen back to within three of Louisiana Tech.
videos.headline: Navy takes to the air for 64-yard TD

videos.description: With one short touchdown run already in the game, Zach Abey keeps the ball and scores again, this time from two yards out to put Navy in front for the first time in the game.
videos.headline: Abey punches it in for 2nd TD of the game

videos.description: Louisiana Tech takes back the lead when Ryan Higgins throws the pass to Carlos Henderson who stays inbounds for the 3-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Henderson keeps the feet inbounds for spinning TD catch

videos.description: Louisana Tech and Navy's mascots compete in dance off
videos.headline: Louisana Tech and Navy's mascots compete in dance off

videos.description: With just under a minute left in the half, Ryan Higgins hits a streaking Trent Taylor down the middle to go 51 yards to the end zone giving Louisiana Tech the lead back at 31-24.
videos.headline: LA Tech strikes for 51-yard TD just before halftime

videos.description: Louisana Tech head coach Skip Holtz discusses explosive offense
videos.headline: Louisana Tech head coach Skip Holtz discusses explosive offense

videos.description: With Navy down a touchdown in the middle of the third quarter, Chris High takes the handoff up the middle and into open space for a 24-yard touchdown to tie the game at 24 against Louisiana Tech.
videos.headline: High takes the handoff 24 yards to the end zone

videos.description: Jarred Craft run for a loss of 5 yards to the Navy 7 Jarred Craft fumbled, forced by Jackson Pittman, recovered by Navy Brandon Jones
videos.headline: Navy forces a fumble on 2nd and Goal

videos.description: Boston Scott takes the handoff and gets through a couple of Navy tackles to find the end zone putting Louisiana Tech back in front 38-31.
videos.headline: Scott slips through for 12-yard LA Tech TD run

videos.description: After Louisiana Tech took the lead in the fourth quarter, Navy answers on the next drive that ends with Chris High's 9-yard run into the end zone to tie the game back up at 38-38.
videos.headline: Navy answers with High's 9-yard TD run

videos.description: Carlos Henderson grabs his second touchdown of the game, this one from 4 yards out, to give Louisiana Tech back the lead at 45-38.
videos.headline: Henderson hauls in incredible TD catch for LA Tech

videos.description: Navy's QB Zach Abey goes down with injury
videos.headline: Navy's QB Zach Abey goes down with injury

videos.description: After quarterback Zach Abey goes off with an injury, Malcolm Perry comes in and on his first play from under center keeps the ball and goes 30 yards to the house to tie the game for Navy at 45-45.
videos.headline: Perry scores 30-yard Navy TD on his first play
